dict.string: Alfred 5 workflow to easily open your projects with your favorite JetBrains product.

if [[ -n "{query}" ]]; then QUERY="{query}" BIN=${jb_bin} PROJECT_NAME=${jb_project_name} if [[ "${jb_is_new_bin}" == "1" ]]; then open -na "${BIN}" --args "${QUERY}" else $(${BIN} "${QUERY}") fi
echo "${PROJECT_NAME}" fi

# reference: https://gist.github.com/cjus/1047794 function jsonval { local json=$1 local var_name=$2
temp=$(echo "$json" | sed 's/\\\\\//\//g' | sed 's/[{}]//g' | awk -v k="text" '{n=split($0,a,","); for (i=1; i<=n; i++) print a[i]}' | sed 's/\"\:\"/\|/g' | sed 's/[\,]/ /g' | sed 's/\"//g' | grep -w "$var_name") echo "${temp##*|}" | cut -d":" -f2 | tr -d "'" }
QUERY="{query}" BIN=$(jsonval $QUERY 'jb_bin') PROJECT_NAME=$(jsonval $QUERY 'jb_project_name')
#Using sed to properly escape spaces in the PROJECT_PATH PROJECT_PATH=$(jsonval "$QUERY" 'arg' | sed 's: :\\ :g' | sed -e 's:\\ : :1')
source ~/.zshrc
eval "${BIN}" "${PROJECT_PATH}"
echo "${PROJECT_NAME}"
